	<div id="Content-Container" data-skip="Content"><div id="Content-Main"><div class="table-div"><div id="Content" class="table-cell">
		<section class="blog-article">

<p>Choosing the right plastic surgeon is one of the most important decisions you will ever make regarding your appearance and health. Whether you are considering a cosmetic enhancement or a reconstructive procedure, the surgeon you select will directly influence your results, safety, and overall experience. With so many practitioners available, it can feel overwhelming to determine who is truly qualified and trustworthy. That is why asking the right questions before committing to any procedure is essential. In this comprehensive guide, we walk you through 15 critical questions you should ask every plastic surgeon before making your decision.</p>

<h2>1. What Are Your Board Certifications?</h2>
<p>Not all doctors who perform plastic surgery are actually board-certified plastic surgeons. Some may be certified in a different specialty entirely, such as dermatology or general surgery. You need to confirm that your surgeon is certified by the appropriate medical board in your country. In India, look for membership in the Association of Plastic Surgeons of India (APSI) or the Indian Association of Aesthetic Plastic Surgeons (IAAPS). A surgeon like <a href="/dr-manoj-k-johar-plastic-reconstructive-surgeon-noida-up/">Dr. Manoj K Johar</a> who holds recognized certifications demonstrates a commitment to the highest standards of training and patient safety. Always verify certifications through official medical council registries rather than taking a surgeon's word at face value.</p>

<h2>2. How Many Years of Experience Do You Have?</h2>
<p>Experience matters enormously in plastic surgery. While a newly qualified surgeon may be talented, there is no substitute for years of hands-on practice. Ask how long the surgeon has been performing the specific procedure you are interested in. A surgeon who has performed thousands of rhinoplasties will handle your case with far greater confidence than one who performs the procedure occasionally. Dr. Johar, for example, brings decades of experience in both cosmetic and reconstructive procedures, giving patients the assurance that they are in skilled hands.</p>

<h2>3. How Many Times Have You Performed This Specific Procedure?</h2>
<p>Beyond general experience, you need to know how frequently your surgeon performs the exact procedure you want. A plastic surgeon who specializes in body contouring may not have the same level of expertise in facial rejuvenation. Ask for a rough number of procedures they have completed in the past year alone. This helps you gauge whether the procedure is a core competency for them or something they perform rarely.</p>

<h2>4. Can I See Before-and-After Photos of Previous Patients?</h2>
<p>Before-and-after photographs are one of the most reliable ways to evaluate a surgeon's skill. Ask to see photos of patients who had the same procedure you are considering, ideally with similar body types or concerns. Pay attention to the consistency of results, the naturalness of the outcomes, and the quality of the scarring. A reputable surgeon will be proud to show you their portfolio and will have no hesitation in sharing these images. You can explore our <a href="/blog/verify-plastic-surgeon-qualified/">guide to verifying surgeon qualifications</a> for more tips on evaluating credibility.</p>

<h2>5. What Are the Potential Risks and Complications?</h2>
<p>Every surgical procedure carries some degree of risk, and an honest surgeon will be transparent about them. Ask specifically about the complication rate for the procedure you want, including infection, scarring, nerve damage, and unsatisfactory results. A surgeon who downplays or dismisses risks entirely is a red flag. You want someone who takes safety seriously and prepares you thoroughly for every possible outcome. Understanding the risks also helps you weigh the benefits against the potential downsides more effectively.</p>

<h2>6. What Type of Anesthesia Will Be Used and Who Administers It?</h2>
<p>Anesthesia plays a critical role in your safety and comfort during surgery. Ask whether the procedure will be performed under general anesthesia, local anesthesia, or sedation. More importantly, find out who the anesthesiologist is and whether they are board-certified. A qualified anesthesiologist with experience in cosmetic procedures is just as important as the surgeon performing the operation. Never assume that anesthesia is a minor part of the process — complications related to anesthesia are among the most serious risks in any surgery.</p>

<h2>7. Where Will the Surgery Be Performed?</h2>
<p>The surgical facility must meet strict safety standards. Ask whether the procedure will be performed in a hospital, an accredited surgical center, or an office-based operating room. Hospital-based facilities typically have the highest safety standards, including access to emergency equipment and post-operative care. <a href="/general-appointment-plastic-reconstructive-surgeon-noida-up/">Dr. Johar's clinic</a> operates in facilities that adhere to stringent safety protocols, ensuring patient well-being at every stage. Confirm that the facility is accredited by recognized health authorities.</p>

<h2>8. What Is the Recovery Process Like?</h2>
<p>Understanding the recovery timeline is crucial for planning your life around the procedure. Ask about expected downtime, when you can return to work, when you can resume exercise, and what activities to avoid during healing. A surgeon who provides detailed recovery instructions and follows up regularly during the healing process demonstrates a commitment to patient care that goes beyond the operating room. Knowing what to expect post-surgery helps you make arrangements for childcare, work leave, and household responsibilities.</p>

<h2>9. What Are the Total Costs and What Do They Include?</h2>
<p>Plastic surgery costs can vary widely, and you need clarity on what is included in the quoted price. Ask whether the cost covers the surgeon's fee, anesthesia, facility charges, pre-operative tests, post-operative garments, and follow-up visits. Be cautious of unusually low prices, as they may indicate corners being cut on safety or quality. A transparent pricing structure reflects a surgeon who values honesty and patient trust. If revision surgery is needed, ask whether that cost is included or additional.</p>

<h2>10. What Happens If I Am Not Satisfied with the Results?</h2>
<p>Even with the most skilled surgeon, outcomes may not always meet expectations. Ask about the surgeon's revision policy. Do they offer complimentary revision procedures if the results are unsatisfactory? What is the timeframe for requesting a revision? A surgeon who stands behind their work will have a clear and fair policy for addressing patient concerns. This question also reveals the surgeon's confidence in their ability and their dedication to patient satisfaction.</p>

<h2>11. Do You Have Testimonials or Reviews from Previous Patients?</h2>
<p>While before-and-after photos show technical skill, patient testimonials reveal the overall experience. Ask for references or direct you to online review platforms where you can read unfiltered feedback from former patients. Look for patterns in the reviews — consistent praise for communication, professionalism, and results is a strong positive signal. Online reviews can also highlight how the surgeon handles complications or dissatisfied patients, which is equally important to know.</p>

<h2>12. How Do You Handle Surgical Complications?</h2>
<p>Complications, though rare with qualified surgeons, can and do occur. Ask how the surgeon manages complications if they arise. Do they have an emergency protocol? Are they available after hours? Do they have hospital privileges where they can admit patients if necessary? A surgeon with a clear and well-practiced complication management plan demonstrates responsibility and preparedness. Knowing this in advance gives you peace of mind and confidence in your surgeon's ability to handle any situation.</p>

<h2>13. Am I a Good Candidate for This Procedure?</h2>
<p>An ethical surgeon will never recommend a procedure that is not in your best interest. Ask whether you are a suitable candidate based on your health, goals, and expectations. A thorough consultation should include a discussion of your medical history, current medications, lifestyle factors, and realistic outcome expectations. If a surgeon agrees to perform a procedure without a comprehensive evaluation, consider it a warning sign. Patient safety should always come first.</p>

<h2>14. What Non-Surgical Alternatives Exist for My Concerns?</h2>
<p>Surgery is not always the only solution. Ask whether there are non-surgical treatments that could achieve similar results with less risk and downtime. Many conditions can be effectively treated with minimally invasive procedures, laser treatments, or injectable therapies. A surgeon who presents all options — not just surgical ones — demonstrates that they prioritize the patient's well-being over financial gain. This approach builds trust and ensures you make a fully informed decision.</p>

<h2>15. How Will You Follow Up After My Surgery?</h2>
<p>Post-operative care is a critical component of a successful surgical outcome. Ask how many follow-up appointments are included, how long the follow-up period lasts, and what to do if you have concerns between visits. A surgeon who provides comprehensive post-operative support shows that their commitment to your care does not end when the surgery is over. Consistent follow-up helps detect and address any issues early, leading to better overall outcomes.</p>

<p>Arming yourself with these 15 questions ensures that you approach your plastic surgery journey with confidence and clarity. The right surgeon will welcome these questions and provide thorough, honest answers. Never rush the decision — take the time to consult with multiple surgeons, compare their responses, and choose the one who makes you feel most comfortable and well-informed. Remember, the goal of any plastic surgery procedure is to enhance your quality of life, and that starts with choosing the right professional to guide you through the process.</p>

